        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/pride-march-trump-second-term-resilience.jpg" alt="People march beneath a giant Pride flag highlighting the community’s resilience and the evolving political context during Trump’s second term" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF"> 
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">
            <i>
            People march beneath a giant Pride flag highlighting the community’s resilience and the evolving political context during Trump’s second term. Credits: Mercedes Mehling</i>
          </p>
        </mj-text>
       
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px " font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">

          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-7-jun-25-sotw-h1-1-pride-month?source=website" target="_blank">Pride Month</a>, celebrated every June, commemorates the anniversary of the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-7-jun-25-sotw-h1-2-1969-stonewall-riots?source=website" target="_blank">1969 Stonewall riots</a>. In the early hours of June 28, police raided New York City’s Stonewall Inn, a known haven for queer people. What followed were several nights of rioting and protests, lasting for about five days.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          One year later, cities like New York, Chicago, Los Angeles, and San Francisco held commemorative marches on the same weekend. These laid the foundation for what would become Pride Month. Pride has grown from a protest into a global celebration of queer identity, resilience, and progress. </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;filter:blur(5px);">
          But over the years, some argue Pride has lost its radical roots. Parades that once demanded justice are dominated by corporations, rainbow branding, and sanitized messaging at the risk of becoming performative. LGBTQ+ rights also face fresh political headwinds. The current administration is working to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-7-jun-25-sotw-h1-3-dismantle-dei-programs?source=website" target="_blank">dismantle DEI programs</a>, calling them “divisive” and “un-American.” </p>
        </mj-text> 
      </mj-column>
